com.hazelcast.util.collection

Class Int2ObjectHashMap<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hazelcast.util.collection.Int2ObjectHashMap<V>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - values stored in the Map
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<Integer,V>

    public class Int2ObjectHashMap<V>
extends Object
implements Map<Integer,V>
    Map implementation specialised for int keys using open addressing and linear probing for cache efficient access.

        public Set<Map.Entry<Integer,V>> entrySet()
        This set's iterator also implements Map.Entry so the next() method can just return the iterator instance itself with no heap allocation. This characteristic makes the set unusable wherever the returned entries are retained (such as coll.addAll(entrySet).
